  </ul>
</article>

<!-- RESPONSE DURING EARTHQUAKE -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>How to Respond During an Earthquake</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>DROP</strong> to the ground.</li>
    <li><strong>COVER</strong> your head and neck under a sturdy table.</li>
    <li><strong>HOLD ON</strong> until the shaking stops.</li>
    <li>Avoid windows, glass, elevators, and heavy objects.</li>
    <li>If outdoors, move to open areas away from buildings and electric poles.</li>
    <li>If driving, stop safely without blocking the road.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- HELPING OTHERS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>How to Help Others After an Earthquake</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Check for your own injuries first, then help others.</li>
    <li>Assist elderly people, children, and persons with disabilities.</li>
    <li>Provide basic first aid for minor injuries.</li>
    <li>Avoid moving seriously injured people unless they are in danger.</li>
    <li>Help create safe evacuation paths.</li>
    <li>Calm others and help prevent panic.</li>
    <li>Report damaged electricity, gas leaks, or structural cracks.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

